slycot._wrapper.ab08nz

slycot._wrapper.ab08nz(n, m, p, a, b, c, d[, equil, tol, lzwork]) = <fortran function ab08nz>

Wrapper for ab08nz.

Parameters

  • n (input int) –

  • m (input int) –

  • p (input int) –

  • a (input rank-2 array('D') with bounds (lda,*)) –

  • b (input rank-2 array('D') with bounds (ldb,*)) –

  • c (input rank-2 array('D') with bounds (ldc,*)) –

  • d (input rank-2 array('D') with bounds (ldd,*)) –

  • equil (input bytes, optional) – Default: ‘N’

  • tol (input float, optional) – Default: 0.0

  • lzwork (input int, optional) – Default: max(min(p,m)+max(3*m-1,n), max(min(p,n)+max(3*p-1,max(n+p,n+m)), min(m,n)+max(3*m-1,n+m)))

Returns

  • nu (int)

  • rank_bn (int)

  • dinfz (int)

  • nkror (int)

  • nkrol (int)

  • infz (rank-1 array(‘i’) with bounds (n))

  • kronr (rank-1 array(‘i’) with bounds (1 + max(n, m)))

  • kronl (rank-1 array(‘i’) with bounds (1 + max(n, p)))

  • af (rank-2 array(‘D’) with bounds (max(1, m + n),n + min(p, m)))

  • bf (rank-2 array(‘D’) with bounds (max(1, n + p),m + n))

  • zwork (rank-1 array(‘D’) with bounds (lzwork))

  • info (int)
